WEBVTT

00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:03.800
"Fruit"

00:00:04.200 --> 00:00:08.066
Five years ago, she quietly planted a seed in my heart.

00:00:08.910 --> 00:00:12.033
And silently, it began to sprout.

00:00:12.733 --> 00:00:15.900
(Episode 1: Seed)
Hey little guy, why are you out here all alone?

00:00:15.900 --> 00:00:17.800
You're completely soaked.

00:00:18.566 --> 00:00:21.433
Let me find something to cover you up.

00:00:22.666 --> 00:00:24.366
I'll come see you again tomorrow.

00:00:24.366 --> 00:00:25.766
Don't go running off, okay?

00:00:31.766 --> 00:00:33.200
Let's not smother him with towels.

00:00:37.246 --> 00:00:38.379
Miss...

00:00:39.666 --> 00:00:40.600
They'll trap the moisture.

00:00:48.500 --> 00:00:50.200
What's it called?

00:00:50.800 --> 00:00:52.233
Does it have a name?

00:00:53.713 --> 00:00:54.744
No.

00:00:54.832 --> 00:00:58.133
How about "Chips"?

00:00:58.133 --> 00:01:00.436
Don't you think it looks like...

00:01:00.437 --> 00:01:01.216
Like snacks?

00:01:01.217 --> 00:01:02.836
Right, exactly!

00:01:02.837 --> 00:01:04.296
Just like snacks!

00:01:04.533 --> 00:01:07.600
From now on, your name is Chips.

00:01:11.765 --> 00:01:12.765
Chips.

00:01:16.566 --> 00:01:17.800
Keep the umbrella.

00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:20.566
Don't get wet.

00:01:22.879 --> 00:01:23.746
Miss.

00:01:25.766 --> 00:01:28.466
So... will you come again tomorrow, Miss?

00:01:29.266 --> 00:01:30.900
I have to be here every day.

00:01:34.899 --> 00:01:36.465
Her words were short

00:01:37.066 --> 00:01:38.600
yet steady.

00:01:38.933 --> 00:01:41.600
Like cutting through the rain.

00:01:42.700 --> 00:01:45.833
Suddenly, I wanted to follow her pace.

00:01:46.066 --> 00:01:47.766
I didn't want to go too fast.

00:01:49.797 --> 00:01:50.666
Chips.

00:01:52.466 --> 00:01:54.833
My teacher said she'll also come tomorrow.

00:02:23.478 --> 00:02:24.766
The outlines are too rigid.

00:02:26.259 --> 00:02:27.493
You're peeking at me drawing.

00:02:29.600 --> 00:02:31.100
I'm looking at the paper.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:33.466
Relax your hand.

00:02:34.500 --> 00:02:35.883
Leave some space for the light.

00:02:45.529 --> 00:02:46.424
Meanie.

00:02:52.766 --> 00:02:54.366
Don't rush to fill it all in.

00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:56.866
Find the shadows first.

00:02:57.500 --> 00:03:02.000
Why do I always want to stare at her face
when she draws?

00:03:02.466 --> 00:03:04.566
It's as if there are so many stories

00:03:04.866 --> 00:03:08.633
casually slipping out from her eyes.

00:03:09.225 --> 00:03:11.066
Then build it up gradually.

00:03:11.366 --> 00:03:13.666
What about the shadow?

00:03:17.412 --> 00:03:18.318
Class dismissed.

00:03:19.533 --> 00:03:21.166
I'll tell you next time.

00:03:31.166 --> 00:03:32.100
(Light

00:03:33.279 --> 00:03:34.516
is a

00:03:37.666 --> 00:03:38.900
decision.)

00:03:40.333 --> 00:03:43.900
Every time she writes, it's like it's about herself.

00:03:44.933 --> 00:03:47.066
Everyone, that's all for today.

00:03:47.066 --> 00:03:49.433
She always speaks so briefly,

00:03:49.900 --> 00:03:52.000
yet I think about it all day.

00:03:53.100 --> 00:03:56.300
Do I care a little too much?

00:03:57.066 --> 00:03:58.500
How strange.